                              "abstract": "Presents a motion planning primitive for car-like vehicles. It is a completely parametrized quintic spline, denoted as eta-spline, that allows interpolation of an arbitrary sequence of points with overall second order geometric G2-continuity. Issues such as minimality, regularity, symmetry, and flexibility of these G2-splines are addressed in the exposition. The development of the new primitive is tightly connected to the flatness based control of nonholonomic car-like vehicles.",
