                      "abstract": "The receding-horizon control strategy provides a relatively simple method for determining feedback control for linear or nonlinear systems: the method is especially useful for the control of slow nonlinear systems, such as chemical batch processes, where it is possible to solve, sequentially, open-loop, fixed-horizon, optimal control problems online. The authors show that the method yields a stable closed-loop system when applied to nonlinear systems.",
